1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,628
[Lara] You killed my parents, didn't you?!

2
00:00:03,712 --> 00:00:04,838
[shouts] Lara!

3
00:00:04,921 --> 00:00:07,090
[suspenseful music playing]

4
00:00:07,173 --> 00:00:11,010
[man] <i>Agent Angeles was found</i>
<i>last night in front of NLEA</i>

5
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:12,679
<i>wrapped in a body bag.</i>

6
00:00:13,346 --> 00:00:14,097
[man] Dead!

7
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:16,433
[Marcus] <i>Did you notice those</i>
<i>subtle glances between General Carillo</i>

8
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:17,851
<i>and Felix earlier?</i>

9
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:20,145
<i>Do you think Felix has anything to do</i>

10
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:21,771
<i>with what the General is doing?</i>

11
00:00:22,355 --> 00:00:24,649
The incident on the ship
wasn't an accident.

12
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:28,611
The MV Emilia was blown up.

13
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:30,864
[Manuel] <i>Mustapha already knows!</i>

14
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:33,033
<i>He has to die!</i>

15
00:00:33,116 --> 00:00:35,160
[explosion]

16
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:36,578
[engines revving]

17
00:00:36,661 --> 00:00:38,038
[gunshots]

18
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:41,207
[rapid gunfire]

19
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,377
[man] <i>Everything happened according</i>
<i>to your plan, General.</i>

20
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:46,004
<i>You're right on schedule, General.</i>

21
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:47,088
Good.

22
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:51,217
[Manuel]
<i>However, there's a snake in our grass.</i>

23
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:53,720
[suspenseful music playing]

24
00:00:53,803 --> 00:00:55,722
What is your husband's name?

25
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:56,890
His name is Victor.

26
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:57,849
[Jamilah] <i>It's Jalil.</i>

27
00:00:57,932 --> 00:01:00,518
<i>He is Doctor Teresa's son, Gabriel.</i>

28
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:03,313
[suspenseful music playing]

29
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:07,942
Cuchy? Is anyone there?

30
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:12,572
[man] <i>You already know</i>
<i>who to deliver these to.</i>

31
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:13,573
[Fernando] <i>Yes, General.</i>

32
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:16,451
[Azuelo]
<i>Reyes has been following General Madrigal,</i>

33
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:19,704
<i>who was sending suitcases of money</i>

34
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:21,289
<i>before he disappeared!</i>

35
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:22,415
[man] <i>If they wanted to kill Reyes,</i>

36
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:23,917
<i>they should have done it right there.</i>

37
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,752
<i>What would they gain by kidnapping him?</i>

38
00:01:25,835 --> 00:01:28,922
<i>They're trying to find out what he knows.</i>

39
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:30,840
[Manuel] <i>Just keep going.</i>

40
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:33,092
He'll give in eventually. [chuckles]

41
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:35,428
[Jalil] <i>Doc, Marcus got kidnapped.</i>

42
00:01:35,512 --> 00:01:37,639
<i>You won't lose another child.</i>

43
00:01:37,722 --> 00:01:39,432
- [Teresa sobs]
- [Jalil] <i>I'm going to look for Marcus.</i>

44
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,893
<i>He'll return home to you safely.</i>

45
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:50,026
[theme music playing]

46
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:05,291
[police 1] Have you heard
about what happened to Agent Reyes?

47
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,043
I just found out earlier!

48
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:09,754
I heard Agent Reyes is missing!

49
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:11,464
[police 2] Who do you think kidnapped him?

50
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:14,134
[police 3] He been stepping
on a lot of toes lately.

51
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:15,051
[police 4] Oh, c'mon.

52
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:17,220
Our organization is just corrupt.

53
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:18,805
[police 5] You're right.

54
00:02:18,888 --> 00:02:21,266
The people have no more fear or respect.

55
00:02:21,349 --> 00:02:23,226
[Jardin] They even chose
Sir Marcus to kidnap.

56
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:24,769
He was always so kind.

57
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:26,396
[Montes scoffs]

58
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:30,859
He’s arrogant.
That’s why he’s being targeted.

59
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:32,277
He's still using his rank to intimidate.

60
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,529
Look at me, I'm just chilling around.

61
00:02:34,612 --> 00:02:35,655
See?

62
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:38,533
[foreboding music playing]

63
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:47,792
Is it true?

64
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:49,460
Was Sir Marcus kidnapped?

65
00:02:50,169 --> 00:02:51,421
I asked for a follow-up.

66
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:52,630
And?

67
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:57,927
[foreboding music continues]

68
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:00,763
[thuds]

69
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:06,686
[tense music playing]

70
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:09,772
We'll find him.

71
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:12,650
We will.

72
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:19,032
[chuckles]

73
00:03:20,658 --> 00:03:21,910
Domingo.

74
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,705
You seem pleased
with what happened to Reyes.

75
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:28,958
Why?

76
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:34,005
[foreboding music continues]

77
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:36,633
Sir.

78
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,552
I've been saying it for a long time…

79
00:03:41,387 --> 00:03:43,681
nothing bad would happen to him.

80
00:03:43,765 --> 00:03:46,351
[tense music playing]

81
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:48,228
You know why?

82
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:51,648
[whispers] Because weeds don't die easily.

83
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:54,317
[tense music playing]

84
00:03:54,943 --> 00:03:55,944
[Felix chuckles]

85
00:03:56,527 --> 00:03:58,238
What did you just say?!

86
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:00,240
[chuckles]

87
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,911
[sucks in teeth]

88
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:11,334
[foreboding music continues]

89
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:21,719
Actually, we're on our way
to Malacañang right now.

90
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,179
I have a meeting with the President.

91
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,931
[interviewer] <i>What's the agenda</i>

92
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,349
<i>for your meeting, General Carillo?</i>

93
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:30,979
The mess that's happening in our country
needs to be put to an end!

94
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:32,772
- A lot of innocent people--
- [engine revvs]

95
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:33,940
[tires screeching]

96
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:35,024
- [thuds]
- [grunts] Argh!

97
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,651
[rapid gunfire]

98
00:04:36,734 --> 00:04:38,945
<i>General? What's going on?</i>

99
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:40,154
[Manuel] We're being ambushed!

100
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,906
<i>General?</i>

101
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,741
[rapid gunfire]

102
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:44,951
[glass breaking]

103
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,037
- [gunshots]
- [moans in pain]

104
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:49,289
[Raquel] General?!

105
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:51,624
[engines revv]

106
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:53,626
General? Hurry!

107
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:54,836
We need to go to the hospital!

108
00:04:54,919 --> 00:04:57,046
[Raquel] Hurry up! General?

109
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:58,298
General?!

110
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:03,136
[suspenseful music playing]

111
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:04,971
[Raquel] Hurry up!

112
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:08,891
General Carillo?!

113
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:12,395
[Jamilah] Miss? Miss? Miss!

114
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:14,939
Miss, excuse me!
We need the patient's details

115
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:16,357
and information!

116
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:19,485
[Teresa] It's a gunshot wound!
I hope it missed any vital organs.

117
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:21,362
Don't touch him!

118
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:23,781
[Teresa] It's a severe wound.
We need to treat it immediately!

119
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,241
Oh, no! No!

120
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,909
He has his own doctor!

121
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:28,786
- He's the only one--
- Please stay here, ma'am.

122
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,580
This isn't allowed!

123
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,040
- He has his own doctor!
- Doctor Reyes!

124
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:34,167
[male doctor] I'll take over.
Sorry for the confusion.

125
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,251
Prep the OR!

126
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,378
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

127
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:39,172
[suspenseful music playing]

128
00:05:39,255 --> 00:05:41,049
[nurse] Hello? Prep the OR.
We have an incoming patient.

129
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:47,972
[suspenseful music continues]

130
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:55,730
<i>In breaking news…</i>

131
00:05:55,813 --> 00:06:00,651
<i>Retired Police General Manuel Carillo</i>
<i>is in critical condition</i>

132
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:04,322
<i>after being ambushed</i>
<i>by unidentified suspects</i>

133
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:08,117
<i>while on his way to a meeting</i>
<i>with President Natalia Mendoza.</i>

134
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,702
<i>It can be recalled that just recently,</i>

135
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:12,705
<i>another high-profile government official,</i>

136
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,540
<i>and the President's close friend,</i>

137
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:17,168
<i>Presidential Chief of Staff Ahmad Mustapha</i>

138
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,670
<i>was killed due to violence.</i>

139
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:21,589
<i>Are we being serious?</i>

140
00:06:21,672 --> 00:06:23,424
<i>The incidents are happening</i>
<i>one after another.</i>

141
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:25,927
<i>They are not just ordinary people.</i>

142
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,221
<i>They are people with power.</i>

143
00:06:28,304 --> 00:06:29,972
<i>The kind where, when they make a decision,</i>

144
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:33,351
<i>people will listen and talk about it.</i>

145
00:06:33,434 --> 00:06:35,895
<i>What's alarming here is that</i>

146
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,647
<i>the perpetrators</i>
<i>are no longer sparing anyone.</i>

147
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:40,900
<i>If we are already worried</i>
<i>about ordinary citizens,</i>

148
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:45,196
<i>what more about these people in power?</i>

149
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:47,073
<i>You know what’s driving me crazy here?</i>

150
00:06:47,156 --> 00:06:51,536
<i>If these powerful people aren't safe,</i>
<i>what about us?</i>

151
00:06:52,411 --> 00:06:54,038
<i>What will happen to us?!</i>

152
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,456
<i>Nothing!</i>

153
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,415
[thuds]

154
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,501
[shouts] <i>Hey, what is this?!</i>

155
00:06:58,584 --> 00:07:00,294
- [thuds]
<i>- Oh my god!</i>

156
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:01,587
[breathes deeply] This is it.

157
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,590
<i>This is what we’ve all been afraid of.</i>

158
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:08,052
<i>At first, the only victims</i>
<i>of this violence</i>

159
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,971
<i>were the Muslim Tausugs,</i>

160
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:11,889
<i>now it's everyone!</i>

161
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:14,976
<i>Even General Carillo has become a victim.</i>

162
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,603
We aren't pointing fingers,

163
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:21,357
<i>If this had been resolved</i>
<i>right from the start…</i>

164
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:26,571
<i>if the massacre on Isla Damai</i>
<i>had been resolved back then,</i>

165
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:28,781
<i>it wouldn't have reached this point.</i>

166
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:33,161
[sighs] <i>Oh, Allah…</i>

167
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,748
After my interview with the two of them,

168
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:40,418
then Presidential Chief of Staff
Ahmad Mustafa

169
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:42,211
was assassinated.

170
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:43,463
And now,

171
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:48,426
it’s Retired Police General Manuel Carillo
who is fighting for his life.

172
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:53,139
I did an exposé on the proliferation
of illegal weapons in the country.

173
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:55,475
But now, I am convinced

174
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,435
that this isn't just about gun-smuggling.

175
00:07:57,518 --> 00:08:00,855
This is an attempt
to overthrow and destabilize

176
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:02,648
a legitimate government.

177
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:06,152
This government, that you,
democratically put in power.

178
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:08,279
That is why we need to be vigilant.

179
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:12,241
The future of our country is at stake.

180
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,784
<i>- Oh no, Mama Loi!</i>
<i>- What is it?</i>

181
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:16,746
<i>What the hell is going on?</i>

182
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:19,582
<i>- Now they're targeting Carillo!</i>
<i>- What?!</i>

183
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:24,003
<i>I still can't fully wrap my head around</i>
<i>what they did to Mustapha,</i>

184
00:08:24,086 --> 00:08:27,298
<i>and now, they have another victim!</i>

185
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:30,092
<i>- Gosh, what a mess!</i>
- [Ogie] <i>You're right.</i>

186
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:32,720
<i>These criminals are no longer</i>
<i>choosing their targets.</i>

187
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:35,681
<i>They're targeting everyone!</i>

188
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:38,643
<i>Hold on. Wait a minute.</i>

189
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:40,561
<i>Let's just make things clear.</i>

190
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:43,606
<i>We are not saying</i>

191
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:47,318
<i>that some deserve violence</i>
<i>more than others.</i>

192
00:08:47,401 --> 00:08:50,738
<i>We must view everyone the same.</i>

193
00:08:50,821 --> 00:08:53,407
<i>- We are all equal.</i>
<i>- You're right.</i>

194
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:54,700
<i>But…</i>

195
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:58,454
<i>Why are you so surprised</i>
<i>that this happened to them?</i>

196
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,540
<i>Of course, we were surprised!</i>

197
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:03,751
<i>If those who hold positions of power,</i>

198
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:06,420
<i>have security</i>
<i>but still get targeted like that,</i>

199
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:10,424
<i>what about us ordinary people?</i>

200
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:13,261
- [Mama Loi] <i>You're right!</i>
- [Ogie] <i>My gosh.</i>

201
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:15,763
<i>No one really deserves that.</i>

202
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:16,806
<i>There's more, Mama Loi.</i>

203
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:18,516
<i>- Oh, what is it?</i>
<i>- Listen.</i>

204
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:20,726
<i>- Oh.</i>
<i>- Have you ever heard</i>

205
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:24,063
<i>that Agent Marcus Reyes--</i>

206
00:09:24,146 --> 00:09:26,607
[squeals] <i>What happened to Agent Marcus?!</i>

207
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:28,484
<i>What happened to Mr. Handsome?!</i>

208
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,152
<i>- I was so surprised!</i>
<i>- What?!</i>

209
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:33,114
<i>- Here's what happened.</i>
<i>- Of course, it's Sir Marcus.</i>

210
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:35,575
<i>- He's missing!</i>
- [gasps]

211
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:38,244
<i>- Where is he?</i>
<i>- He obviously isn't with me!</i>

212
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:41,914
<i>That is why we are calling on</i>
<i>to Sir Marcus--</i>

213
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,457
<i>wherever you are,</i>

214
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,710
<i>I hope they find you soon,</i>

215
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:48,629
<i>- and we hope you're safe!</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

216
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:50,047
<i>- Right?</i>
<i>- Wait a minute.</i>

217
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:52,174
<i>Why are you more concerned</i>
<i>about his safety?</i>

218
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,927
<i>Because it's Agent Marcus!</i>

219
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,095
<i>You're right.</i>

220
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:58,681
<i>We hope you're safe, Agent Marcus.</i>

221
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:01,976
[tense music playing]

222
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:08,190
Doc, Marcus was kidnapped.

223
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,320
[Jalil] <i>Don't worry about it, okay?</i>

224
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:15,031
- [sobs]
- You won't lose another child.

225
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:16,282
[crying]

226
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:18,701
I'll find him.

227
00:10:18,784 --> 00:10:20,995
He'll return home to you safely.

228
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:25,958
[morose music playing]

229
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:32,298
[crying]

230
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:37,720
[morose music continues]

231
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:42,475
[melancholic music playing]

232
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:46,228
[sighs heavily]

233
00:10:49,565 --> 00:10:50,900
[door clicks]

234
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:55,821
Doctor?

235
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,033
Hmm?

236
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:00,701
Umm…

237
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:03,579
Are they looking for me

238
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,622
in the ER?

239
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,750
No, Doctor.

240
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:13,130
I just wanted to check on you.

241
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,593
Is there any news on Sir Marcus?

242
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:21,138
Nothing.

243
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:23,766
[melancholic music continues]

244
00:11:25,059 --> 00:11:25,935
After…

245
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,979
After Allan told me the news last night…

246
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:31,482
that my son was kidnapped…

247
00:11:31,565 --> 00:11:33,401
they still haven't found him.

248
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:37,321
- Doc…
- [crying]

249
00:11:37,988 --> 00:11:41,242
Don't worry, Doctor.

250
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:47,081
I'm sure the TFA is doing
everything they can to find him.

251
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:51,210
Doc, they won't abandon him.

252
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,339
Especially Major Espina.

253
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,220
- Calm down, Doctor.
- [crying]

254
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,889
It's okay, Doctor.

255
00:12:05,474 --> 00:12:07,268
[crying] My son…

256
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:15,734
[Jamilah] <i>I feel guilty</i>
<i>because I can't tell Jalil the truth.</i>

257
00:12:16,735 --> 00:12:19,321
<i>The person in danger…</i>

258
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:22,533
<i>Sir Marcus, is his own brother.</i>

259
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:26,704
<i>I didn't like keeping secrets,</i>
<i>but I have to make a choice.</i>

260
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:30,166
[in Tausug] <i>I'm sorry, Jalil,</i>

261
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,960
<i>but I need to protect you.</i>

262
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:35,004
[melancholic music continues]

263
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,132
- It's okay.
- [crying]

264
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:40,676
Don't worry.

265
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,973
[Jalil] Right there.

266
00:12:46,056 --> 00:12:47,516
That's where they took Reyes.

267
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:49,894
But where did they take him?

268
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,854
That is exactly what
I am wondering about, sir.

269
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:55,065
Because… I already checked
the nearby streets,

270
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:57,568
but I couldn't find anything, sir.

271
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:00,070
It's impossible for him
to just disappear like that.

272
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:01,572
I agree, sir.

273
00:13:01,655 --> 00:13:03,199
It's clean. There really isn't a trace.

274
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:06,577
We need to know where they took Reyes.

275
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:10,748
[Usman] Don't worry.

276
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:14,418
The TFA is already on the ground
to look for Marcus.

277
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:15,920
But what do we do now, sir?

278
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:19,256
We've checked all the CCTV footage,
but we got nothing.

279
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:21,133
Play it again.

280
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:22,801
- From the very beginning.
- Okay, sir.

281
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,178
[Jalil] Play it again.

282
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:26,680
[keyboard clacks]

283
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,277
Hey, did you see anything?

284
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,279
Nothing. How about you?

285
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:45,241
Nothing.

286
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:47,535
The people who took him left no trace.

287
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:49,662
This can't be happening.

288
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,665
We need to find Sir Marcus immediately.

289
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:54,833
Before they even kill him.

290
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:10,474
This is the only road
Sir Marcus' kidnappers could've passed.

291
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,478
But they didn't see anything
on the CCTV footage.

292
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,397
Which route might they have taken?

293
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:20,526
Hold on.
Why is Sir Felix not here with us?

294
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:21,735
Oh, yeah.

295
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:24,405
I haven't seen Sir Felix today.

296
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:25,990
He's at the S.Trinidad hospital.

297
00:14:26,073 --> 00:14:27,741
He's assigned
to General Carillo's security.

298
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:31,120
[tense music continues]

299
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:32,454
[music fades]

300
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:38,460
[somber music playing]

301
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,636
[Felix]
<i>Your father, Datu Rahman, is free now.</i>

302
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:52,266
<i>And your brother, Jalil Abubakar,</i>
<i>has already cleared his name.</i>

303
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:54,810
<i>The authorities are no longer after him.</i>

304
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:56,854
<i>But…</i>

305
00:14:57,771 --> 00:14:59,899
<i>why hasn't he turned up yet?</i>

306
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:02,443
<i>Where are you, Jalil?</i>

307
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:05,237
<i>What are you up to?</i>

308
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:08,782
<i>You, Jamilah Abubakar…</i>

309
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:12,286
<i>you are the key to everything.</i>

310
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:25,007
[somber music continues]

311
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:32,598
[chuckles evilly]

312
00:15:35,684 --> 00:15:42,066
[suspenseful music playing]

313
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:44,276
[water splashes]

314
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:48,405
[Marcus coughing, wheezing]

315
00:15:55,788 --> 00:16:00,376
[Marcus breathing heavily]

316
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:03,212
[grunting] Argh! Argh!

317
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,798
[panting]

318
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:08,008
[in distorted voice]
I'll repeat my question.

319
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:10,344
What do you know?

320
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:12,680
What did Mustapha tell you?

321
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:14,848
Get out of there!

322
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:17,768
Show yourself!

323
00:16:19,019 --> 00:16:19,895
[Marcus] You're an animal!

324
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,146
[electricity buzzing]

325
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:22,272
[Marcus screams] Aah!

326
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:24,525
[Marcus grunts] Argh!

327
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:29,363
[grunting continues]

328
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:35,077
[breathing heavily]

329
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:38,038
[groans]

330
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:40,666
[in distorted voice]
You really won't talk, huh?

331
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:47,006
- [electricity buzzing]
- [Marcus grunting]

332
00:16:56,432 --> 00:16:58,600
[Marcus breathing heavily]

333
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:03,022
[in distorted voice]
Let's see how tough you are.

334
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:11,321
- [electricity buzzing]
- [Marcus grunting]

335
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:16,660
[Marcus shaking]

336
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:23,625
[grunting continues]

337
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:31,175
[body thuds]

338
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:37,181
[suspenseful music continues]

339
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:53,405
[music turns pensive]

340
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:04,750
[man] Miss, this is
for Major Allan Espina.

341
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:05,709
It's urgent.

342
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:08,170
Okay, sir. I'll just log it. Hold on.

343
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:10,422
Can I get your name? Who is it from?

344
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,341
[receptionist] Sir?

345
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:17,930
[pensive music continues]

346
00:18:23,018 --> 00:18:24,812
[Jalil sighs exasperatedly]

347
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:29,483
[Jalil breathes deeply]

348
00:18:39,701 --> 00:18:41,245
Is it you, Madrigal?

349
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:42,996
Did you kidnap Reyes?

350
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:46,875
Where did you take him?

351
00:18:52,297 --> 00:18:53,549
[knocks on door]

352
00:18:56,677 --> 00:18:57,970
Come in.

353
00:18:58,053 --> 00:18:59,179
[door opens]

354
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:02,099
Sir, this came for you.

355
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:03,517
It says here it's urgent.

356
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,185
I came straight here.

357
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:06,979
[Jalil] Thank you.

358
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:23,412
[music turns tense]

359
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:30,627
[traffic noise]

360
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,048
You really didn't see anything?

361
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,259
Thank you, sir.

362
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:44,266
[indistinct dialogue from a distance]

363
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:57,029
[cellphone buzzing]

364
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:02,367
They want us back at HQ.

365
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:03,327
[cellphone buzzing]

366
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,374
Let's go.

367
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:23,889
[tense music continues]

368
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,057
[music fades]

369
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,975
He's always been a good mentor to me.

370
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:28,018
[solemn music playing]

371
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:29,937
Both he and Ahmad.

372
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:33,273
[Raquel] Madam.

373
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:35,817
He wanted nothing but to protect you.

374
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:40,614
Especially after
Sir Mustapha's assassination.

375
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,824
[music turns tense]

376
00:20:43,825 --> 00:20:44,826
I know.

377
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:48,205
And for that, I will be forever grateful.

378
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:55,337
Raquel.

379
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:57,923
Let me know as soon as he wakes up.

380
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:01,843
Thank you, Madam President.
I'll keep you posted.

381
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,602
[footsteps retreating]

382
00:21:11,186 --> 00:21:12,396
[door opens]

383
00:21:26,994 --> 00:21:33,750
[tense music continues]

384
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:53,437
[stirring music playing]

385
00:22:00,861 --> 00:22:02,321
[young Gabriel] <i>Marcus!</i>

386
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:04,448
<i>Marcus!</i>

387
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:06,199
<i>Wake up!</i>

388
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,077
<i>Wake up, Marcus!</i>

389
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:11,955
<i>Marcus! Wake up!</i>

390
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:15,876
<i>Marcus! Wake up!</i>

391
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:18,086
<i>Wake up, Marcus!</i>

392
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:20,255
<i>Marcus!</i>

393
00:22:22,215 --> 00:22:24,968
<i>Please wake up. You got this, Marcus.</i>

394
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:31,349
<i>Marcus, please wake up!</i>

395
00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:35,437
[young Gabriel crying]
<i>Wake up, Marcus! You got this!</i>

396
00:22:36,772 --> 00:22:37,981
[Marcus grunts]

397
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:43,111
[weakly] Gabriel…

398
00:22:44,404 --> 00:22:45,447
Gabriel…

399
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:52,079
Marcus, don't give up! You got this!

400
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:54,915
<i>Marcus, you got this!</i>

401
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:57,834
[Marcus inhales]

402
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:00,587
Gabriel, where are you?

403
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:02,798
Ga--

404
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:04,841
Gabriel.

405
00:23:05,801 --> 00:23:06,968
Gabriel.

406
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:08,345
[breathing heavily]

407
00:23:08,428 --> 00:23:09,596
Where are you?

408
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:20,482
[stirring music continues]

409
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:38,792
[Jamilah] <i>Father has decided.</i>

410
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:40,752
I'm scared to face Jalil.

411
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:42,796
<i>But he has a right to know the truth.</i>

412
00:23:42,879 --> 00:23:45,382
Jalil is kind, and he loves you very much.

413
00:23:45,465 --> 00:23:48,176
[Jamilah] <i>I'm sure he'd understand</i>
<i>why you've done it.</i>

414
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:52,305
[Manuel] We've no way to find out
what Ahmad told him!

415
00:23:52,389 --> 00:23:54,474
And who his accomplices were!

416
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:56,226
What are we going to do to Reyes?

417
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:57,519
Kill him!

418
00:23:57,602 --> 00:24:01,022
An intel came earlier
regarding the whereabouts of Agent Reyes.

419
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:02,524
How can we make sure it's accurate?

420
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:04,609
- Who is it from, sir?
- I am willing to take the risk.

421
00:24:05,193 --> 00:24:07,237
[Felix] <i>They're on to me already.</i>

422
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:11,074
<i>I need to start getting rid of them.</i>

423
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:16,454
[gunshots]

424
00:24:17,247 --> 00:24:20,083
[young Gabriel] Marcus! Marcus! Marcus!

425
00:24:22,377 --> 00:24:23,295
[Marcus] <i>Gabriel?</i>

426
00:24:23,378 --> 00:24:26,798
[theme music ends]
